h3. Problem Definition

Questions users cannot post a question if third-party cookies are blocked on their browsers with the following error:
{code:none}
Uncaught SecurityError: Failed to read the 'localStorage' property from 'Window': Access is denied for this document
{code}
 
 !Screenshot 2018-02-22 17.11.14.png|thumbnail!

This happens if user changes their browser setting to block third-party cookies.
 Since Question is implemented as add-on and its resources is hosted on the different domain from Confluence Cloud, users should enable third-party cookies.

However, the problem is Questions users cannot realise they need to change the setting.
h3. Suggested Solution

Detect if localStorage is available and show the friendly notice not to block third-party cookies.
{code:none}
if (typeof window.localStorage !== 'undefined') {
    // SETUP SESSION, AUHT, LOCALE, SETTINGS ETC
} else {
    // PROVIDE FEEDBACK TO THE USER
}
{code}
h3. Workaround
 * For a Chrome user: go to chrome://settings/content/cookies (_Settings_ > _Content settings_ > _Cookies_), and make sure to enable "Allow local data to be set (recommended)" and disable "Block third-party cookies"
 ** !Screenshot_2018-02-22_16_43_42.png|thumbnail!

h3. Related Documents
 * [The Chromium Projects|https://www.chromium.org/for-testers/bug-reporting-guidelines/uncaught-securityerror-failed-to-read-the-localstorage-property-from-window-access-is-denied-for-this-document]
 * [Issue #32 · GoogleDeveloperExperts/experts-app-backend · GitHub|https://github.com/GoogleDeveloperExperts/experts-app-backend/issues/32]
 * [https://stackoverflow.com/q/30481516/879951]

h3. Summary

Users are not able to compare history versions from pages with huge changes between versions.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a new page in your instance and add content;
 # Make a lot of changes;
 # Compare the two versions;

h3. Expected Results
 * Changes comparison will load as expected.

h3. Actual Results
 * Pages will fail to load and give the following Error:
{code}
Comparing these versions exceeded the timeout of 30 seconds.
{code}

Workaround
 * no workaround

h3. Summary

Users are not able to like a page from the *Like* button at the notification e-mail.
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Create a new page in your instance;
 # Check your email;
 # Click on the like button from the email notification;

h3. Expected Results
 * Pages will load as expected.

h3. Actual Results
 * Pages will fail to load and give a 403 Error:

{code:java}
Access to <your instnace>.atlassian.net was denied
You don't have authorization to view this page.
HTTP ERROR 403 {code}
h3. Console error:
{code:java}
Failed to load resource: the server responded with a status of 403() like.action{code}
h3. Workaround
 * Access the page through the instance UI and click the like button

h3. Summary
Issues created from the Create multiple issues from table option on the Product Requirements page will cut the issues' descriptions when using Spanish language.

h3. Environment
Confluence Cloud;
Browser configured to Spanish.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Set Browser's and Confluence's language to spanish;
# Create a new page using the Product requirements template;
# On the requirements table, fill multiple cells on the notes column to have more than 255 characters;
# Select any text from the table and click on the Jira logo (create issue);
# Select 'Create multiple issues from table' and chose the Notes row to be the Description field;

h3. Expected Results
The issues should be created with the full description text, as it is when using English.

h3. Actual Results
The created issues will have their descriptions cut  to 255 characters and a '...' at the end. 

h3.Workaround
Set browser's language to English
